'''Albert Stanislaus Gérard''' (1920-1996) was a Belgian scholar of [[comparative literature]], specializing in [[African literature]].<ref>Chantal Zabus, 'Albert S. Gérard', ''Research in African Literatures'', Vol. 29, No. 1 (Spring, 1998), pp.199-201</ref>
==Works== * ''L'idée romantique de la poésie en Angleterre. Étude sur la théorie de la poésie chez Coleridge, Wordsworth, Keats et Shelley'', 1955. Translated as ''English romantic poetry : ethos, structure, and symbol in Coleridge, Wordsworth, Shelley, and Keats'', 1968 * ''Four African literatures: Xhosa, Sotho, Zulu, Amharic'', 1971 * (ed.) ''Black Africa'', 1972 * ''African language literatures : an introduction to the literary history of Sub-Saharan Africa'', 1981 * ''European-language writing in sub-Saharan Africa'', 1985 * ''Contexts of African literature'', 1990
