{{Infobox album | name = TK1998 LATEST WORKS | type = EP | artist = [[Tetsuya Komuro]] | cover = | alt = | released = November 26, 1998 | recorded = | venue = | studio = | genre = [[Pop music|Pop]] / [[Electronica]] | length = | label = [[Sony Music Entertainment Japan|SMEJ]] | producer = | prev_title = | prev_year = | next_title = | next_year = }}
'''''TK 1998 Latest Works''''' was a mini-album of the Japanese composer/producer [[Tetsuya Komuro]]. He composed and arranged the songs, meanwhile [[Marc Panther]] wrote the lyrics and sang in the songs. [[Olivia Lufkin|OLIVIA]] was the backs up vocalist in the songs "Welcome to the Museum", "Dreams" and "Empty lies". Despite [[Tetsuya Komuro]] being under [[Avex]], the mini-album was released under [[Sony Music Entertainment Japan|SMEJ]].
==Track listing== # Welcome to the Museum # Transformation # Dreams # 8 # Empty lies {{DEFAULTSORT:Tk 1998 Latest Works}} [[Category:Olivia Lufkin songs]] [[Category:Museums in popular culture]] [[Category:1998 EPs]]

{{italic title}}{{RefImprove|date=April 2018}}

'''''The Vermont Ghost Guide''''' is a comprehensive paranormal travel guide published in 2000<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://www.worldcat.org/oclc/42812921|title=The Vermont ghost guide|last=A.|first=Citro, Joseph|date=2000|publisher=University Press of New England|isbn=1584650095|location=Hanover, NH|oclc=42812921}}</ref> that documents all of the major [[haunting]]s and ghost-sightings in [[Vermont]], inspired by the numerous Vermont wildlife and destination guides. The book was researched and written by Vermont [[folklore]] expert [[Joseph A. Citro|Joe Citro]] and illustrated by [[Horror fiction|horror]] artist and fellow Vermonter [[Stephen R. Bissette|Steve Bissette]]. The book is divided into sections, each devoted to a single region of Vermont and its supposed [[undead]] residents. Like his other non-fiction books, Citro does not speculate on whether or not the paranormal occurrences he describes are in fact true, but instead leaves that job entirely to the reader. However, as a joke, Citro did insert one account that was a complete fabrication, although he has never revealed which one that may be.{{Citation needed|date=April 2018}}

